Write a general summary of a book described below. The Secret Garden by Frances Hodgson Burnett is a classic childrenâ€™s book about discovering the joy of friendship and nature. It tells the story of Mary Lennox, a young girl who moves from India to England to live with her uncle after the death of her parents. Mary is a spoiled brat who resents the family she moves in with and the dreary English countryside. But when she discovers a secret garden, she discovers a new life full of adventure, love, and friendship.
